  "about": {
    "lead": "Executive with an operator's instinct and an entrepreneur's bias for building. I've led brand, partnerships, and marketing functions from inception across seed-stage startups and multi-billion dollar platforms.",
    "body": [
      "My career has run from Experiential to Cultural Marketing to IP Licensing, but the throughline is always the same: figure out how a brand builds a real relationship with the people who care about it, then build the infrastructure to make that scalable.",
      "At StockX I spent five years going from building experiential programs to running global cultural marketing — activations at NBA Finals and Paris Fashion Week, the DropX product pipeline, charitable work raising over $1M. At Ghostwrite I came in as the first partnerships person and built the licensing operation that now runs 30+ concurrent deals across major sports leagues and cultural brands.",
      "I studied Cultural Marketing and Movements at NYU's Gallatin School, where you design your own major because no existing department quite covers it. That felt right then and still does."
    ],
